<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1896,2029]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1436,151,320]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,218,1896,1921]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Notes</emphasis>
. The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1893" box="[353,504,1896,1921]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Leptopholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[353,504,1896,1921]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Leptopholcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been revised recently (
<bibRefCitation author="Huber, B. A." box="[806,943,1896,1921]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 509" refId="ref27101" refString="Huber, B. A. (2011) Revision and cladistic analysis of Pholcus and closely related taxa (Araneae, Pholcidae). Bonner zoologische Monographien, 58, 1 - 509." type="journal article" year="2011">Huber 2011</bibRefCitation>
); it has a wide distribution in tropical Africa and Asia (
<bibRefCitation author="Huber, B. A." box="[267,406,1932,1957]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 509" refId="ref27101" refString="Huber, B. A. (2011) Revision and cladistic analysis of Pholcus and closely related taxa (Araneae, Pholcidae). Bonner zoologische Monographien, 58, 1 - 509." type="journal article" year="2011">Huber 2011</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Huber, B. A. &amp; Carvalho, L. S. &amp; Benjamin, S. P." box="[419,635,1932,1957]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="432 - 450" refId="ref27172" refString="Huber, B. A., Carvalho, L. S. &amp; Benjamin, S. P. (2014 a) On the New World spiders previously misplaced in Leptopholcus: molecular and morphological analyses and descriptions of four new species (Araneae, Pholcidae). Invertebrate Systematics, 28, 432 - 450. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / IS 13050" type="journal article" year="2014">
Huber 
<emphasis box="[497,555,1932,1957]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">et al.</emphasis>
2014a
</bibRefCitation>
, 2018). All known representatives are leaf-dwellers. Only two species seem to occur in 
<collectingCountry box="[355,472,1968,1993]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
: the widespread and possibly introduced 
<taxonomicName authority="(Simon, 1893)" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1893" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1893" box="[953,1336,1968,1993]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Leptopholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="podophthalmus">
<emphasis box="[953,1158,1968,1993]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">L. podophthalmus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Simon, E." box="[1176,1327,1968,1993]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="256 - 488" refId="ref28518" refString="Simon, E. (1893) Histoire Naturelle des Araignees. 1 (2). 2 nd edition. Roret, Paris, 233 pp. [pp. 256 - 488]" type="book chapter" year="1893">Simon, 1893</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and the Western Ghats-Sri Lankan endemic 
<taxonomicName authority="Huber, 2011" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2011" box="[558,804,2004,2029]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Leptopholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kandy">
<emphasis box="[558,655,2004,2029]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">L. kandy</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Huber, B. A." box="[662,804,2004,2029]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 509" refId="ref27101" refString="Huber, B. A. (2011) Revision and cladistic analysis of Pholcus and closely related taxa (Araneae, Pholcidae). Bonner zoologische Monographien, 58, 1 - 509." type="journal article" year="2011">Huber, 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The two species are easily distinguished in the field: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2011" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Leptopholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="11" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kandy">
<emphasis italics="true" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">L. kandy</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a long worm-shaped abdomen (as in most species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1893" box="[864,1015,151,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Leptopholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[864,1015,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Leptopholcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1893" box="[1038,1241,151,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Leptopholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="podophthalmus">
<emphasis box="[1038,1241,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">L. podophthalmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a relatively short one (compare 
<figureCitation box="[311,440,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 42–46" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1900,1923]" captionTargetBox="[164,1427,373,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[164,1427,373,1888]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 42–46. Leptopholcus, live specimens. 42–44. L. kandy Huber, 2011, male from Ethagala, female from near Belilena Cave, and male from Kitulgala. 45–46. L. podophthalmus (Simon, 1893), male from Kandy, and male from Mapalena Ella sharing web with cecidomyiid flies." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2625044/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Figs 42, 45</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1893" box="[460,791,188,213]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Leptopholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="podophthalmus">
<emphasis box="[460,791,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Leptopholcus podophthalmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a phylogenetically isolated species (
<bibRefCitation author="Eberle, J. &amp; Dimitrov, D. &amp; Valdez-Mondragon, A. &amp; Huber, B. A." box="[1226,1429,188,213]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="141" refId="ref26630" refString="Eberle, J., Dimitrov, D., Valdez-Mondragon, A. &amp; Huber, B. A. (2018) Microhabitat change drives diversification in pholcid spiders. BMC Evolutionary Biology, 18, 141. https: // doi. org / 10.1186 / s 12862 - 018 - 1244 - 8" type="journal article" year="2018">
Eberle 
<emphasis box="[1308,1364,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
) that ranges from 
<collectingCountry box="[344,455,223,248]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
to southern 
<collectingCountry box="[597,664,223,248]" name="China" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">China</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[721,838,223,248]" name="Singapore" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Singapore</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2011" box="[849,1075,223,248]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Leptopholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kandy">
<emphasis box="[849,1075,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Leptopholcus kandy</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most closely related with the Southeast Asian 
<taxonomicName authority="Deeleman-Reinhold, 1986" authorityName="Deeleman-Reinhold" authorityYear="1986" box="[340,795,260,285]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Leptopholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borneensis">
<emphasis box="[340,491,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">L. borneensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Deeleman-Reinhold, C. L." box="[499,795,260,285]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="45 - 48" refId="ref26338" refString="Deeleman-Reinhold, C. L. (1986) Leaf-dwelling Pholcidae in Indo-Australian rain forests. In: Eberhard, W. G., Lubin, Y. D. &amp; Robinson, B. C. (Eds.), Proceedings of the Ninth International Congress of Arachnology, Panama 1983. Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington, D. C., pp. 45 - 48." type="book chapter" year="1986">Deeleman-Reinhold, 1986</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Huber, 2011" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2011" box="[850,1135,260,285]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Leptopholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="huongson">
<emphasis box="[850,989,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">L. huongson</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Huber, B. A." box="[996,1135,260,285]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="1 - 509" refId="ref27101" refString="Huber, B. A. (2011) Revision and cladistic analysis of Pholcus and closely related taxa (Araneae, Pholcidae). Bonner zoologische Monographien, 58, 1 - 509." type="journal article" year="2011">Huber, 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Huber, B. A." box="[1150,1287,260,285]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="1 - 509" refId="ref27101" refString="Huber, B. A. (2011) Revision and cladistic analysis of Pholcus and closely related taxa (Araneae, Pholcidae). Bonner zoologische Monographien, 58, 1 - 509." type="journal article" year="2011">Huber 2011</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Eberle, J. &amp; Dimitrov, D. &amp; Valdez-Mondragon, A. &amp; Huber, B. A." pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="141" refId="ref26630" refString="Eberle, J., Dimitrov, D., Valdez-Mondragon, A. &amp; Huber, B. A. (2018) Microhabitat change drives diversification in pholcid spiders. BMC Evolutionary Biology, 18, 141. https: // doi. org / 10.1186 / s 12862 - 018 - 1244 - 8" type="journal article" year="2018">
Eberle 
<emphasis box="[1380,1436,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
